# Go Backend Conventions

- Keep backend code inside `backend/internal/`.
- Domain packages should follow `handler.go`, `service.go`, `model.go`.
- Handlers should stay thin: parse request, call service, return JSON.
- Use `pgx` with raw SQL. Do not introduce an ORM.
- Use typed app errors via `internal/apperrors`.
- Keep route registration centralized in `cmd/server/main.go`.
- Prefer constructor injection (`NewService`, `NewHandler`) over globals.
- Keep migration files as numbered SQL pairs in `internal/db/migrations/`.

## Eva Board specifics

- Domain packages live under `backend/internal/`: `board`, `board/agent`, `board/triage`, `codegen`, `github`, `llm`
- Coding agent CLIs are wrapped behind the `codegen.Agent` interface — never call `claude` directly outside `internal/codegen/`
- The autonomous loop (verify, review, retry, auto-PR) lives in `internal/board/agent.go` — keep retry caps configurable
- Real-time updates use SSE (`internal/board/events.go`), not WebSocket
- GitHub API access goes through `internal/github/` — never call the GitHub API from other packages
- LLM calls go through `internal/llm/` — never instantiate HTTP clients to OpenRouter from other packages
